(44, 17, 29, 24, 10, 4, 10, 'the Godhead is like unto gold, or silver, or stone', 'Idolatry and the True God', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of idols made by human hands, contrasting them with the greatness of God. Acts 17:29 warns against thinking of God as similar to these man-made objects, while Jeremiah 10:4-10 describes the limitations and worthlessness of such idols.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
