(44, 17, 30, 60, 4, 3, 3, 'commandeth all men every where to repent', 'Call to Repentance and Change', 'Both passages emphasize the need for repentance and a departure from past sinful behaviors. Acts 17:30 highlights God''s command for all to repent, while 1 Peter 4:3 reflects on the past life of sin that believers are called to leave behind.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 30, 44, 3, 19, 19, 'commandeth all men every where to repent', 'Call to Repentance', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of repentance. Acts 17:30 states that God commands all men to repent, while Acts 3:19 urges repentance for the blotting out of sins.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 31, 40, 25, 31, 46, 'judge the world in righteousness', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment, where Acts 17:31 speaks of God judging the world in righteousness, and Matthew 25:31-46 describes the Son of Man judging the nations. This connection highlights the accountability of individuals based on their actions towards others.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 31, 45, 2, 16, 16, 'judge the world in righteousness', 'Judgment by Jesus Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of God''s judgment through Jesus Christ. Acts 17:31 mentions God judging the world in righteousness by the ordained man, while Romans 2:16 refers to God judging the secrets of men by Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 31, 61, 3, 7, 7, NULL, 'Judgment Day Connection', 'Both passages emphasize a future day of judgment, where the world will be judged in righteousness. Acts 17:31 speaks of assurance through resurrection, while 2 Peter 3:7 refers to the day of judgment reserved for ungodly men.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 31, 19, 9, 8, 8, 'judge the world in righteousness', 'Judgment in Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine judgment executed in righteousness. Acts 17:31 speaks of God judging the world through the ordained man, while Psalms 9:8 affirms that He will judge the world in righteousness.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 31, 19, 98, 9, 9, 'judge the world in righteousness', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine judgment and righteousness. Acts 17:31 speaks of God judging the world in righteousness, while Psalms 98:9 mentions judging the earth with righteousness.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 31, 47, 5, 10, 10, 'judge the world in righteousness', 'Judgment and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of judgment, with Acts 17:31 mentioning a day of judgment by the ordained man, while 2 Corinthians 5:10 speaks of appearing before the judgment seat of Christ. This connection highlights the accountability of individuals for their actions.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 31, 46, 4, 5, 5, 'judge the world in righteousness', 'Judgment and Revelation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine judgment and revelation. Both passages emphasize that God will judge the world and reveal hidden truths at the appointed time.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 32, 44, 17, 18, 18, 'the resurrection', 'Connection of Resurrection Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the resurrection, with Acts 17:18 introducing it as a point of contention among philosophers, and Acts 17:32 showing the varied reactions to this teaching. This connection highlights the significance of the resurrection in early Christian preaching.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 32, 44, 26, 8, 8, 'resurrection of the dead', 'Resurrection of the Dead', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of resurrection, with Acts 17:32 presenting a reaction to the idea and Acts 26:8 questioning disbelief in it. This connection highlights the differing responses to the notion of God raising the dead.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 32, 46, 4, 10, 10, NULL, 'Foolishness and Mockery in Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of being perceived as foolish for one''s faith. In Acts, some mocked the resurrection, while in 1 Corinthians, Paul acknowledges being seen as a fool for Christ''s sake.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 32, 47, 6, 2, 2, NULL, 'Resurrection and Salvation Timing', 'This connection highlights the urgency of responding to the message of salvation, as seen in both passages. Acts 17:32 reflects a moment of decision regarding the resurrection, while 2 Corinthians 6:2 emphasizes the present opportunity for salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 32, 14, 36, 16, 16, 'mocked', 'Mocking of God''s Messengers', 'Both passages emphasize the mocking of God''s messengers. In Acts, some mocked the resurrection message, paralleling the disdain shown in 2 Chronicles towards the prophets. This connection highlights a recurring theme of rejection faced by those delivering God''s word.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 32, 42, 14, 18, 18, NULL, 'Excuses and Rejection of Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection in both passages. In Acts, some mocked the resurrection, while in Luke, individuals made excuses to avoid responding to an invitation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 32, 58, 3, 7, 8, NULL, 'Response to God''s Message', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of responding to God''s message. In Acts, some mocked the resurrection, while Hebrews warns against hardening hearts to God''s voice.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 34, 44, 17, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection Between Areopagus References', 'Both passages emphasize the Areopagus as a significant location where discussions about new doctrines occur. The mention of Dionysius the Areopagite in Acts 17:34 indicates a direct link to the earlier reference of the Areopagus in Acts 17:19.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 34, 45, 11, 5, 6, 'believed', 'Remnant of Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of a remnant of believers who respond to God''s grace. In Acts, certain men believed, paralleling the idea in Romans of a remnant according to the election of grace.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 34, 44, 13, 48, 48, 'believed', 'Connection of Belief and Ordination', 'Both passages emphasize the act of belief among individuals. In Acts 17:34, certain men believed, while Acts 13:48 notes those ordained to eternal life believed.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 34, 23, 55, 10, 11, 'believed', 'The Power of God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the effectiveness of God''s word in bringing forth belief, as seen in Acts where certain men believed. Similarly, Isaiah emphasizes that God''s word will accomplish its purpose, paralleling the transformative impact of the message preached by Paul.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 34, 40, 20, 16, 16, 'believed', 'Belief and Chosen Status', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief leading to being chosen. In Acts 17:34, those who believed, including Dionysius, reflect the idea in Matthew 20:16 that while many are called, few are chosen.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 34, 43, 7, 48, 52, 'believed', 'Belief and Skepticism', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in Jesus among different groups. In Acts, Dionysius and others believe, while in John, the Pharisees express skepticism about Jesus'' origins.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 34, 43, 19, 38, 42, NULL, 'Discipleship and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of belief and discipleship. In Acts, Dionysius and Damaris represent new believers, while Joseph of Arimathea and Nicodemus are secret disciples of Jesus, highlighting the varied responses to faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 1, 46, 1, 2, 2, 'Paul departed from Athens, and came to Corinth', 'Connection Between Paul and Corinth', 'This connection highlights Paul''s journey to Corinth, where he later addresses the church in his letter. Both passages emphasize the significance of Corinth in Paul''s ministry.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
