(44, 18, 5, 44, 9, 22, 22, 'Jesus was Christ', 'Proclamation of Jesus as Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the act of testifying and proving that Jesus is the Christ. In Acts 18:5, Paul testifies to the Jews, while in Acts 9:22, Saul confounds the Jews by proving the same truth.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 5, 26, 3, 14, 14, 'pressed in the spirit', 'Connection of Spiritual Pressures', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''pressed in the spirit'' in Acts and the ''heat of my spirit'' in Ezekiel. Both passages emphasize the intense emotional and spiritual experiences of the individuals as they respond to divine prompting.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 5, 18, 32, 18, 20, 'pressed in the spirit', 'Connection of Constrained Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of being compelled by the spirit to speak. In Acts, Paul is ''pressed in the spirit,'' while in Job, the speaker states, ''the spirit within me constraineth me.'' This connection highlights the urgency and necessity of expressing one''s message.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 5, 24, 6, 11, 11, 'pressed in the spirit', 'Divine Urgency in Proclamation', 'This connection highlights the urgency in both passages. In Acts, Paul is ''pressed in the spirit'' to testify, paralleling Jeremiah''s expression of being ''full of the fury of the Lord'' and weary of restraint.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
