(44, 18, 6, 26, 33, 4, 4, 'Your blood be upon your own heads', 'Responsibility for One''s Actions', 'Both passages emphasize personal accountability for one''s choices. In Acts, Paul declares that the consequences of rejection are on the listeners, similar to Ezekiel''s warning about the consequences of ignoring the trumpet''s sound.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
