(44, 18, 8, 46, 1, 13, 17, 'believed on the Lord with all his house', 'Baptism and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of baptism and belief in Christ. Crispus is mentioned in both contexts, highlighting his significance in the early church''s growth.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 8, 41, 16, 15, 16, NULL, 'Belief and Baptism Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief leading to baptism. Both passages emphasize that belief in the Lord is essential for salvation, as seen in Crispus''s belief and the directive to preach and baptize in Mark.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 8, 45, 10, 14, 17, 'believed on the Lord', 'Faith Through Hearing', 'This connection highlights the process of belief and faith. In Acts, Crispus and others believed after hearing the message, paralleling Romans, which emphasizes that faith comes by hearing the word of God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
